==English==
===Noun===
#(''US, Australia'') A business where [[movie]]s are [[project]]ed onto a huge [[outdoor]] [[screen]], and patrons remain in their vehicles, listening either by a [[speaker]] or a designated radio frequency.
#(''US'') A restaurant where patrons remain in their vehicles and order food and beverages via a speaker phone; their meal is brought to their vehicle by a waitress.
#: ''The teen-agers went down to the '''drive-in''' to order some hamburgers and fries.''
#(''US, Australia'') Shortened form of [[drive-in movie]] or [[drive-in restaurant]].

